info.name: Record Linker Postman Collection
info.description:
This is the Postman Collection for testing out some of the Record Linker API endpoints.

See the full API documentation by spinning up the Record Linker Docker container and visiting [http://localhost:8000/api/redoc](http://localhost:8000/api/redoc).

### What is Record Linker?

Record Linker is an open-source tool that uses a configurable, multi-phase algorithm to efficiently link and deduplicate patient records across public health systems and jurisdictions.

The DIBBs Record Linker is designed to streamline patient matching and record deduplication — both within disease surveillance systems and across internal tools (e.g., surveillance, vital records, and immunization information systems) — functioning as a Master Patient Index (MPI) to unify records for the same individual across datasets. Record Linker enables jurisdictions to reduce missed patient matches and avoid false positives, so staff only review the records that truly need human judgment.

At Record Linker’s core is a best-in-class algorithm that combines statistical probabilities with configurable rules to improve patient match accuracy and transparency. Jurisdictions can fine-tune review thresholds to strike the right balance between automation and manual oversight. With an API-driven architecture, Record Linker integrates easily into existing public health infrastructure or can function independently as a standalone MPI solution.

To learn more about Record Linker, visit [https://github.com/CDCgov/RecordLinker.](https://github.com/CDCgov/RecordLinker.)

### Benefits of Record Linker

- **More complete and accurate records** – Improves data quality by linking patient data across surveillance, immunization, and other public health systems, reducing duplicate records and missed matches.
    
- **Greater efficiency in manual review** – Enhances match confidence and transparency, thereby avoiding unnecessary reviews and unmerging efforts
    
- **Reduced administrative burden** – Automates matching where possible, minimizing the workload associated with merging, unmerging, and reconciling records.
    
- **Improved workload management** – Enables jurisdictions to set matching thresholds to balance automation with manual review based on staffing and processing capacity.
    
- **Better coordination across jurisdictions** – Facilitates secure, automated record matching between states and localities, reducing reliance on manual processes.
